summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on the United Nations Mission of Observers in Prevlaka (UNMOP), 
Having considered the Secretary-General's report of 28 June 2002,

Reaffirms Croatia's independence, sovereignty, and territorial integrity; 
Notes the Joint Declaration of 30 September 1992, and the Agreement on Normalization of Relations between Croatia and the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia of 23 August 1996; 

1. Authorizes UNMOP to continue monitoring the demilitarization of the Prevlaka peninsula until 15 October 2002; 
2. Calls on parties to cease violations of the demilitarized regime, cooperate with UNMOP, and ensure observers' safety and freedom of movement; 

3. Welcomes progress in normalization of relations between Croatia and the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia; 
Urges parties to accelerate efforts towards a negotiated settlement on Prevlaka; 

4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
